%N A002091 From a Goldbach conjecture: the location of records in A185091.
%C A002091 A stronger version of the second Goldbach conjecture (every odd number can be expressed as the sum of 3 primes) states that every odd number k > 5 can be written as k = 2*p + q, p, q prime. The conjecture was posed by E. Lemoine and later by H. Levy. The article by B. H. Mayoh assumes q {1,prime}. For the representations of k minimizing q, the sequence gives the value of k at which a larger q than for all representations of j < k is required. The new record value of q is given in A002092. The corresponding sequences for q prime and q=1 excluded are A194828 and A194829. - _Hugo Pfoertner_, Sep 03 2011
%C A002091 k is in this list when (k+1)/2 is the index of a record in A185091.
%C A002091 Checked up to k=10^13. a(50) is > 10^13. - _Hugo Pfoertner_, Sep 25 2011
